  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Syria&#x2019;s Future: Improving Quality of  Access to Educational Opportunities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Given the level of destruction within Aleppo City and the movements of the population over the past months, PUI will respond to the needs of conflict-affected children through an integrated intervention responding to the needs in terms of Education and Child Protection.

The Overall Objective of the proposed project is to support and enhance the educational opportunities available to conflict-affected children and adolescents within Aleppo City.

More specifically, PUI aims to:

	Improve access to and quality of education through the implementation of Remedial Classes to support drop out students to re-enroll in formal education, and reduce the risk of low-performing students from dropping out
	Establish Child Protection Children&#x2019;s Clubs, integrated within the Remedial Classes, to enhance awareness of child protection issues, and provide healthy, secure environment for school-aged children to discuss potential risks through one-on-one and group counseling sessions
	Ensure Capacity Building of MOE staff to better respond to the specific needs of conflict-affected children
	Raise Awareness on Child Protection issues (topics include CRC, Child Labor, Early Marriage etc) within the educational facilities and the community to reduce the potential protection risks for children
	Classroom Rehabilitations, including integration of WASH facilities, to provide protective, inclusive, quality learning environments equipped with teaching and learning materials benefiting conflict-affected school-aged children.
	Vocational Training courses, targeting adolescents (15-20) unable to return to formal education in order to build income generating capacity and be inserted into the private sector.</narrative>
  </description>
